# TypeScript Configuration Template

## Purpose

Configure the TypeScript compiler - target JavaScript version, module system, strictness, and path mappings. Essential for any TypeScript project.

## Official Documentation

- [TSConfig Reference](https://www.typescriptlang.org/tsconfig) - All compiler options
- [Project References](https://www.typescriptlang.org/docs/handbook/project-references.html) - Monorepo setup
- [Module Resolution](https://www.typescriptlang.org/docs/handbook/modules/theory.html) - How TS finds modules

## When to Use

- ✅ Any TypeScript project
- ✅ JavaScript projects wanting type checking (with `checkJs`)
- ✅ Projects with `.ts`, `.tsx`, `.mts`, `.cts` files

## When NOT to Use

- ❌ Pure JavaScript projects (unless you want JSDoc checking)
- ❌ Non-Node/browser JavaScript runtimes with incompatible type systems

## Required Marker Files

- `package.json`
- `*.ts` or `*.tsx` files

## Trade-offs & Alternatives

| Alternative | When to Use Instead |
|-------------|---------------------|
| JSDoc types | Type checking without TypeScript compilation |
| No types | Very small scripts, prototypes |

## Template

### Node.js Application

```json
{
  "$schema": "https://json.schemastore.org/tsconfig",
  "compilerOptions": {
    // Output
    "target": "ES2022",
    "module": "NodeNext",
    "moduleResolution": "NodeNext",
    "outDir": "dist",
    "rootDir": "src",

    // Strictness
    "strict": true,
    "noUncheckedIndexedAccess": true,
    "noImplicitOverride": true,

    // Interop
    "esModuleInterop": true,
    "allowSyntheticDefaultImports": true,
    "forceConsistentCasingInFileNames": true,

    // Emit
    "declaration": true,
    "declarationMap": true,
    "sourceMap": true,

    // Skip
    "skipLibCheck": true
  },
  "include": ["src/**/*"],
  "exclude": ["node_modules", "dist"]
}
```

### React/Next.js Application

```json
{
  "$schema": "https://json.schemastore.org/tsconfig",
  "compilerOptions": {
    // Output
    "target": "ES2022",
    "lib": ["DOM", "DOM.Iterable", "ES2022"],
    "module": "ESNext",
    "moduleResolution": "Bundler",
    "jsx": "preserve",

    // Strictness
    "strict": true,
    "noUncheckedIndexedAccess": true,

    // Interop
    "esModuleInterop": true,
    "allowSyntheticDefaultImports": true,
    "forceConsistentCasingInFileNames": true,
    "isolatedModules": true,

    // No emit (bundler handles it)
    "noEmit": true,

    // Skip
    "skipLibCheck": true,

    // Path aliases
    "baseUrl": ".",
    "paths": {
      "@/*": ["./src/*"]
    }
  },
  "include": ["src/**/*", "next-env.d.ts"],
  "exclude": ["node_modules"]
}
```

