## Key Options Explained

### Module System

| Setting | Use For |
|---------|---------|
| `"module": "NodeNext"` | Node.js with ESM |
| `"module": "CommonJS"` | Node.js with CJS |
| `"module": "ESNext"` | Bundlers (Vite, webpack) |

| Resolution | Use For |
|------------|---------|
| `"moduleResolution": "NodeNext"` | Node.js |
| `"moduleResolution": "Bundler"` | Vite, webpack, etc. |

### Strictness Levels

```json
// Minimum recommended
{
  "strict": true
}

// Maximum safety
{
  "strict": true,
  "noUncheckedIndexedAccess": true,
  "noImplicitOverride": true,
  "exactOptionalPropertyTypes": true
}
```

### Path Aliases

```json
{
  "compilerOptions": {
    "baseUrl": ".",
    "paths": {
      "@/*": ["./src/*"],
      "@components/*": ["./src/components/*"],
      "@utils/*": ["./src/utils/*"]
    }
  }
}
```

Note: Bundlers need separate alias config (Vite, webpack, etc.)

